  "text": "Simple hybrid ORR proposals, known as ORR-Norm and ORR-SIR depending on the type of CQI that mobiles report, were introduced in [CITATION_1] as improved versions of pure ORR scheme. These hybrid schedulers guarantee a certain degree of fairness by selecting the primary user according to its waiting time in transmission and exploit multiuser diversity in the selection of the secondary semiorthogonal user. Thus, achievable sum rate in this situation is now given by",
